description: Molly Weasley: "Your sons flew that car to Harry’s house and back last night! What have you got to say about that, eh?" ... Fred, George, and Ron Weasley flying to the Burrow after rescuing Harry Potter from 4 Privet Drive. The Flying Ford Anglia was used on 3 August 1992 by Fred, George, and Ron Weasley to rescue Harry Potter, who was locked up in his room at the Dursleys' and had been unable to receive any mail from the Wizarding community as a result of Dobby's attempts to protect him.
title: Flying car

description: The MacBook is a brand of Macintosh laptop computers designed and marketed by Apple Inc. that use Apple's macOS operating system since 2006. It replaced the PowerBook and iBook brands during the Mac transition to Intel processors, announced in 2005. The current lineup consists of the MacBook Air (2008–present) and the MacBook Pro (2006–present). Two different lines simply named "MacBook" existed from 2006 to 2012 and 2015 to 2019.
title: My School Mac
